# Tech Stack Reference

## Core Framework
- **Next.js 14.2.29** — App Router only. No Pages Router. No `getServerSideProps` / `getStaticProps`.
- **TypeScript strict mode** — all files, no `any` unless absolutely justified with a comment
- **React 18** — server components by default, client components explicitly marked with `"use client"`

## Database & Auth
- **Supabase** with `@supabase/ssr` (NOT the legacy `@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs`)
- Two clients:
  - `lib/supabase/client.ts` → browser client (use in client components)
  - `lib/supabase/server.ts` → server client (use in server components, API routes)
- Never import the server client in a client component. Never import the browser client in a server component.
- RLS is enabled on all tables — never bypass with service role key in client-side code

## AI
- `@anthropic-ai/sdk` — model: `claude-sonnet-4-6`
- System prompt: `"You are Spectral Intelligence, an AI analyst for the Spectral drone threat platform."`
- Wrapper: `lib/claude/client.ts` — use `querySpectral()`, don't call the SDK directly from components
- Max tokens: 2048

## 3D Globe / Scenario Engine
- **CesiumJS 1.116.0** — used for the Red/Blue Arena module only
- **Critical**: CesiumJS requires `ssr: false` dynamic import. NEVER import CesiumJS at the top level.
- CESIUM_BASE_URL must be set and webpack config must copy Workers/Assets/ThirdParty/Widgets
- See `next.config.ts` for the CopyWebpackPlugin configuration — do not break it
- `components/arena/CesiumArena.tsx` is the only CesiumJS consumer

## Visualisation
- **D3.js 7.9.0** — EW spectrum chart (`components/spectrum/SpectrumChart.tsx`)
- **Recharts 2.12.7** — secondary charts (platform comparisons, radar range plots)
- **Mapbox GL JS 3.4.0** — 2D intel overview panel only (secondary to Cesium)

## UI Libraries
- **Tailwind CSS** with custom Spectral design tokens (see `tailwind.config.ts`)
- **Radix UI** primitives — use for accessible dialogs, dropdowns, tooltips
- **Lucide React 0.383.0** — icons only (no Heroicons, no FontAwesome)
- **Framer Motion** — route transitions and module card animations
- **Zustand** — global state (scenario config, selected platform, active filters)
- **react-hot-toast** — notifications

## Package Manager
- `npm` — use `npm install`, not `yarn` or `pnpm`

